com.camerontec.catalys.util.fast.template.instruction

Interface IStopBitDecoder

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    NonNullableStopBitDecoder, NullableStopBitDecoder

    public interface IStopBitDecoder
    Common interface for classes that decode stop bit delimited values from a FAST stream.
    Author:
    John Cameron

    • Method Detail

      • decodeByteVector

        ITagValue decodeByteVector(IFastDecodableMessage msg)
                    throws IOException
        Decode byte vector from stream.

        Any non null value found in stream is returned as the value part of an ITagValue object retrieved from the free pool of the given message.

        Note that this will never return an isNone() value - it will always return null instead.

        Parameters:
        msg - Message from whose free pool any returned ITagValue is retrieved.
        Returns:
        Decoded value or null
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem reading the stream.

      • setInputStream

        void setInputStream(InputStream input)
        Associates an input stream with the decoder.
        Parameters:
        input - Input stream from which values are decoded.

      • setLogStream

        void setLogStream(OutputStream logStream)
        Associates an output stream with the decoder.

        If present, all bytes read from the decoder's input stream will be copied to this log stream.

        May be null - in which case no logging occurs (the default).

        Parameters:
        logStream - Output stream where input bytes are logged.

      • setSpy

        void setSpy(ISpy spy)
        Associates a spy with the decoder.

        Parameters:
        spy - a spy. May be null - in which case no spy is associated (the default).
